aar.  It's well known by now that rare spells maintain their value over time because once they are scribed, they leave the economy forever.<br>
<br>
Why not do something similar with gear/weapons?  Like if you went to the bazaar and bought Centi Shortsword #5,973,256 for 50pp for your twink.  Then your twink goes up to an NPC and performs a quick &quot;Hail&quot; quest that turns the CSS into a NO DROP item.  In return for permanently removing said item from the economy you would get a slight improvement over  it's original stats or a bonus to the dmg/dly ratio.<br>
<br>
They did something similar, if much more convoluted, with the SMR for the enchanter epic and it's worked pretty well.  It's one of the few old world items from a relatively low level dungeon that still nets around 4kpp(or more). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seaotter42>SeaOtter42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 12:41 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cure for gear mudflation?</span><hr size=1> mudflation isnt even a real problem. As more and more items become available in the game, old items face more competition for characters money. additionally, these older items become easier and easier to obtain, thus increasing supply of the particular item. Not every item will be useful forever. This actually helps new players a lot, as obtaining entry level gear becomes easier, and it doesn't hurt experienced players, as how many level 60-65s still spend their time hunting in lower guk? I would even contend that mudflation helps lower levels, who otherwise would be faced with large numbers of higher level players farming items in areas intended to be hunted by mid-low level characters. <br>
<br>
