Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilsainsilverback>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 862<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 1:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cure for gear mudflation?</span><hr size=1> Putting restrictions on items now being sold cheaply in the bazaar, but twenty + levels higher than a person could obtain as a drop, would effectively remove them from the game.  Players would just sell them to vendors, vs. the bazaar.<br>
<br>
Lets see, my level 5 Paladin can kill enough spiderlings to get a stack of silks, which sells for 20pp.  For 20pp, he can buy two velium weapons in the bazaar, that are 30+ levels higher than he is.  That is just wrong.  Let's remove those items from the game, so that people aren't farminig for plat, but actually level appropriate items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gemlin>Gemlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 484<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 1:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cure for gear mudflation?</span><hr size=1> Theres a very different situation here.<br>
<br>
First of all Comparing Level 60 Spells to Weapons.<br>
<br>
By saying this Weapon that you can buy off twink so and so goes for 50 plat why does Sunstrike (For example) go for 20k+?<br>
<br>
Reason : The level 60 spells drop off Kunark Dragons Generally or something equally difficult to get. These mobs also have a spawn rate of 5+ days!<br>
<br>
When a Centi Longsword drops off a mob like gore, then I could expect to see the prices stay high. Look at the Windblades in HOH. They go for a randsom now!! WHY? Because they are a ultra rare drop!<br>
<br>
Look at Sceptres of Destruction .. Same thing, they go for a lot! Why? Rarity and on most servers, they dont drop anymore.<br>
<br>
Look at the Blade of Carnage. They go for a randsom also! Why? Because it drops off a Difficult mob.<br>
